00:37:05.460 --> 00:37:06.980
My name's Micah Anderson.

00:37:06.980 --> 00:37:11.100
I'm the senior meditation
instructor at MBA.

00:37:11.100 --> 00:37:15.900
We have the 10 to
12 module curriculum

00:37:15.900 --> 00:37:18.360
that we use with the youth.

00:37:18.360 --> 00:37:20.750
The first kind of
foundational one

00:37:20.750 --> 00:37:23.390
is introduction to mindfulness.

00:37:23.390 --> 00:37:27.370
So for example, the way we would
introduce that to the youth

00:37:27.370 --> 00:37:31.200
would be through a game called
Still Chillin', which is,

00:37:31.200 --> 00:37:34.460
essentially it's a competition
to kind of see who can sit

00:37:34.460 --> 00:37:36.850
still the longest.

00:37:36.850 --> 00:37:41.230
And generally, a class
would be 8 to 10 kids,

00:37:41.230 --> 00:37:43.070
somewhere around there.

00:37:43.070 --> 00:37:46.590
And slowly, we'll play like
five or six rounds sometimes.

00:37:46.590 --> 00:37:53.080
And slowly we'll start to
introduce some instruction

00:37:53.080 --> 00:37:56.640
in the actual game.

00:37:56.640 --> 00:38:01.030
And it's a great way for them
to start to find just focus.

00:38:01.030 --> 00:38:02.760
Usually it's a visual, right?

00:38:02.760 --> 00:38:06.220
They'll find a piece and they'll
just kind of sit and just

00:38:06.220 --> 00:38:07.670
focus on it, right?

00:38:07.670 --> 00:38:10.010
And then slowly people
will start laughing

00:38:10.010 --> 00:38:11.230
and get knocked out.

00:38:11.230 --> 00:38:15.890
And there's always like last
man standing kind of thing.

00:38:15.890 --> 00:38:19.280
And then as the curriculum moves
forward, and a lot of times

00:38:19.280 --> 00:38:22.850
we have a cohort model,
which we'll move through.

00:38:22.850 --> 00:38:25.630
And each module builds
on the next one.

00:38:25.630 --> 00:38:27.970
So we'll talk about
basic goodness.

00:38:27.970 --> 00:38:31.320
And then the next module would
go into impulse regulation,

00:38:31.320 --> 00:38:36.920
just kind of unpacking how
mindfulness can support

00:38:36.920 --> 00:38:38.890
impulses and reactivity.

00:38:38.890 --> 00:38:42.970
And the difference between
a reaction and a response.

00:38:42.970 --> 00:38:45.740
And then it really
starts to go deeper.

00:38:45.740 --> 00:38:48.920
We do start to go into things
like emotional intelligence

00:38:48.920 --> 00:38:54.260
and awareness, and how we can
use that self moment to moment

00:38:54.260 --> 00:38:59.360
presence to look at emotions.

00:38:59.360 --> 00:39:04.350
And then eventually look at some
difficult emotions and trauma.

00:39:04.350 --> 00:39:09.994
And will impact what
empathy is, and compassion,

00:39:09.994 --> 00:39:14.410
and try and unearth
beliefs that the youth may

00:39:14.410 --> 00:39:17.070
have about themselves,
whether negative or positive.

00:39:17.070 --> 00:39:20.881
And then trying to
address those if possible.

00:39:20.881 --> 00:39:22.380
So those would be
some of the areas.

00:39:22.380 --> 00:39:26.050
And we use loving
kindness meditations.

00:39:26.050 --> 00:39:28.840
We use a variety
of different types

00:39:28.840 --> 00:39:32.320
