00:41:10.910 --> 00:41:14.119
and this joy and
happiness comes.

00:41:14.119 --> 00:41:15.910
And of course, it's
all impermanent, right?

00:41:15.910 --> 00:41:18.000
It comes and it goes.

00:41:18.000 --> 00:41:18.615
It passes.

00:41:21.250 --> 00:41:23.060
I don't know the
answer to how it's

00:41:23.060 --> 00:41:24.940
connected to emotional
pain, because I also

00:41:24.940 --> 00:41:27.710
have had so much emotional
pain in my experience.

00:41:27.710 --> 00:41:33.120
And I think-- I tend to
think that emotional pain is

00:41:33.120 --> 00:41:36.535
unavoidable for all
of us human beings.

00:41:39.570 --> 00:41:42.230
That it's just part of having
a mind , having a heart,

00:41:42.230 --> 00:41:43.870
having emotions.

00:41:43.870 --> 00:41:48.510
That we have unpleasant,
afflictive, emotional pain.

00:41:48.510 --> 00:41:53.710
And some people have the
deep traumatic experience

00:41:53.710 --> 00:41:57.390
that Micah was talking about
with many of the students

00:41:57.390 --> 00:42:01.320
that we're working
with in the juvies.

00:42:01.320 --> 00:42:02.280
Maybe some of us.

00:42:02.280 --> 00:42:05.640
I know myself, I've had a
lot of traumatic experience

00:42:05.640 --> 00:42:07.740
in my life, and a lot
of emotional pain.

00:42:07.740 --> 00:42:11.670
But I don't know how or if it
equates to the development.

00:42:11.670 --> 00:42:16.210
I tend to think of
the phenomena of joy,

00:42:16.210 --> 00:42:22.330
rapture, that that is a
universal outcome of training

00:42:22.330 --> 00:42:23.620
the mind.

00:42:23.620 --> 00:42:26.230
That in a deep
meditative discipline,

00:42:26.230 --> 00:42:30.340
you get concentrated enough,
it's just what happens.

00:42:30.340 --> 00:42:31.615
Joy will arise.

00:42:34.260 --> 00:42:42.090
Gratitude, gladness, these
pleasure states will happen.

00:42:42.090 --> 00:42:45.880
And I would imagine
that whether or not

00:42:45.880 --> 00:42:50.960
you've had a lot, kind of an
extra dosage of emotional pain,

00:42:50.960 --> 00:42:53.100
or actually you've had
a life that hasn't had--

00:42:53.100 --> 00:42:57.500
you've had the normal
human suffering [LAUGHS]

00:42:57.500 --> 00:42:59.730
that we all have.

00:42:59.730 --> 00:43:01.700
But it hasn't been
extreme in any way.

00:43:01.700 --> 00:43:05.247
I'd imagine that there--
I feel like-- I don't

00:43:05.247 --> 00:43:07.580
know if it's true or not, but
I feel like those are just

00:43:07.580 --> 00:43:10.857
sort of universal
qualities that happen

00:43:10.857 --> 00:43:13.190
as part of the phenomenon of
deep meditative discipline.

00:43:15.990 --> 00:43:17.982
Yeah.

00:43:17.982 --> 00:43:19.260
AUDIENCE: Can I [INAUDIBLE]?

00:43:19.260 --> 00:43:20.343
NOAH LEVINE: Yeah, please.

00:43:20.343 --> 00:43:21.940
