00:43:26.380 --> 00:43:28.830
AUDIENCE: In your journey,
which very touching

00:43:28.830 --> 00:43:33.320
journey of managing pain, your
emotional pain, at what point

00:43:33.320 --> 00:43:36.690
did your ability to-- I'm
guessing at some point

00:43:36.690 --> 00:43:38.590
you developed the
ability to access joy.

00:43:38.590 --> 00:43:40.730
And at what point
did that become

00:43:40.730 --> 00:43:46.140
helpful as part of the journey
towards overcoming pain?

00:43:46.140 --> 00:43:48.735
And if so, how so?

00:43:48.735 --> 00:43:50.360
NOAH LEVINE: It's
hard for me to answer

00:43:50.360 --> 00:43:53.270
because, like I was saying
in that first question,

00:43:53.270 --> 00:43:56.330
it happened so gradually for me.

00:43:56.330 --> 00:43:59.300
I can't point to, like oh, and
then there was this moment.

00:43:59.300 --> 00:44:01.960
But I do, reflecting
back, and say, oh,

00:44:01.960 --> 00:44:04.470
those first couple of
years I was doing the-- I

00:44:04.470 --> 00:44:06.380
wanted the kindness
or the compassion

00:44:06.380 --> 00:44:08.610
or the joy, the
appreciative joy,

00:44:08.610 --> 00:44:10.810
but it wasn't really happening.

00:44:10.810 --> 00:44:12.830
I wasn't even able to,
in my own inner voice,

00:44:12.830 --> 00:44:15.860
be sincere about what these
well wishing practices.

00:44:18.510 --> 00:44:22.620
But at a couple years,
started to shift.

00:44:22.620 --> 00:44:26.480
At five years into my
practice, I could see it really

00:44:26.480 --> 00:44:28.560
starting to shift.

00:44:28.560 --> 00:44:32.880
I can remember about 10 years
into my meditation practice

00:44:32.880 --> 00:44:35.240
where I had the experience
for the first time

00:44:35.240 --> 00:44:39.220
in my life of
forgiving everyone.

00:44:39.220 --> 00:44:40.940
Up to that point,
I had resentments

00:44:40.940 --> 00:44:45.010
that I was trying to let go
of, but hadn't let go of.

00:44:45.010 --> 00:44:47.080
I had made some progress,
progress, progress,

00:44:47.080 --> 00:44:52.550
but there was still those couple
that we're just no, not yet.

00:44:52.550 --> 00:44:55.490
And then coming to this moment
about 10 years into meditation

00:44:55.490 --> 00:44:58.970
practice where I'd forgiven
everyone, including myself.

00:44:58.970 --> 00:45:02.240
And I could think of even the
worst people in the world,

00:45:02.240 --> 00:45:05.440
I could think of them
with some compassion,

00:45:05.440 --> 00:45:08.030
with some forgiveness.

00:45:08.030 --> 00:45:11.330
And seeing them as
suffering, confused beings.

00:45:14.340 --> 00:45:17.950
And that was joyous.

00:45:17.950 --> 00:45:19.300
And I can remember that.

00:45:19.300 --> 00:45:21.830
But I can also-- it was an
interesting experience for me,

00:45:21.830 --> 00:45:24.230
because there was also a
delusion of permanence.

00:45:24.230 --> 00:45:27.460
I thought, I'm done.

00:45:27.460 --> 00:45:29.314
Forgiveness, did it.

00:45:29.314 --> 00:45:31.250
[LAUGHTER]

00:45:31.250 --> 00:45:33.350
Totally done.

00:45:33.350 --> 00:45:38.690
And then I was a little
bit surprised the next day

00:45:38.690 --> 00:45:40.530
when I was pissed off again.

00:45:40.530 --> 00:45:42.560
I thought I was done
with these resentments?

00:45:42.560 --> 00:45:44.280
I thought I'd forgiven.

00:45:44.280 --> 00:45:46.300
And then see, oh,
even that forgiveness,

00:45:46.300 --> 00:45:51.500
even that joyous experience
of liberation from hatred

00:45:51.500 --> 00:45:53.760
was temporary.

00:45:53.760 --> 00:45:56.670
It was real, but it
was really impermanent

00:45:56.670 --> 00:45:59.390
like every other mind
state or emotion.

00:46:02.520 --> 00:46:06.870
So for me, pretty gradual.

00:46:06.870 --> 00:46:10.010
Sometimes it's hard to tell,
also, inside ourselves.

00:46:10.010 --> 00:46:14.080
Other people might
be able to-- Micah

00:46:14.080 --> 00:46:18.020
might be able-- me and Micah
have been friends for 25 years.

00:46:18.020 --> 00:46:22.580
He might be able to say, yeah,
around seven years he was less

00:46:22.580 --> 00:46:24.296
of a jerk.

00:46:24.296 --> 00:46:25.420
He was happier or whatever.

00:46:28.310 --> 00:46:32.590
Sometimes the people outside
of us can say, you're happier.

00:46:32.590 --> 00:46:35.340
And inside, we're
not always totally

00:46:35.340 --> 00:46:36.635
clear about when that happened.

00:46:39.150 --> 00:46:44.190
How do we navigate the balance
between generosity and kindness

00:46:44.190 --> 00:46:47.710
and compassion and forgiveness
and healthy boundaries?

00:46:47.710 --> 00:46:52.260
And when it's too
much, overtaxing on us,

00:46:52.260 --> 00:46:55.230
or I think you ended with
then we're resentful.

00:46:55.230 --> 00:46:57.849
Like we've been too
forgiving, and we're not

00:46:57.849 --> 00:46:58.890
taking care of ourselves.

00:46:58.890 --> 00:47:05.460
Or too generous and not
taking care of ourselves.

00:47:05.460 --> 00:47:08.200
It's a wonderful question.

00:47:08.200 --> 00:47:11.010
It's a very important question.

00:47:11.010 --> 00:47:13.720
And like a lot of these
really deep and important

00:47:13.720 --> 00:47:16.240
personal questions for us.

00:47:16.240 --> 00:47:20.200
Like there's absolutely a
line of what's too much.

00:47:20.200 --> 00:47:23.880
When are we being complacent
rather than active?

00:47:23.880 --> 00:47:26.640
When are we becoming
a doormat, because I'm

00:47:26.640 --> 00:47:28.360
being compassionate
toward your suffering

00:47:28.360 --> 00:47:30.480
so I'm going to let
you be unkind to me.

00:47:30.480 --> 00:47:33.130
And I'm going to be
compassionate and forgiving.

00:47:33.130 --> 00:47:36.430
There's absolutely
a line of when

00:47:36.430 --> 00:47:38.700
we need to actually
speak up for ourselves,

00:47:38.700 --> 00:47:43.500
and say no, and have
a good boundary.

00:47:43.500 --> 00:47:47.630
But I don't know where that
line is for anybody else.

00:47:47.630 --> 00:47:49.130
Because it's for each one of us.

00:47:49.130 --> 00:47:54.270
It's our personal, where's
the balance here for me.

00:47:54.270 --> 00:47:57.250
And so it's a lot of what the
mindfulness practice and all

00:47:57.250 --> 00:48:00.960
of this conversation is about
is developing that intuitive

00:48:00.960 --> 00:48:05.456
knowing of what's too much.

00:48:05.456 --> 00:48:09.260
And I think we get there
from trial and error.

00:48:09.260 --> 00:48:15.330
I think the only way that we
found our balance, our middle,

00:48:15.330 --> 00:48:19.200
is through giving too
much, giving not enough,

00:48:19.200 --> 00:48:24.330
